(firstQuint)Study to Investigate Effects of a Herbal Drug Compared to Placebo on Sleep.

 To demonstrate the influence of the herbal combination preparation Neurapas(R) balance on the objective sleep structure in comparison with placebo.

 A further aim was to investigate whether treatment with Neurapas(R) balance versus placebo brings about an improvement in attention and well-being and whether these changes are related to the improvement in the sleep structure.

 1.

 Does the administration of 3 x 2 Neurapas(R) balance tablets over a period of three days vs.

 placebo lead to an improvement in continuity of sleep? 2.

 Does the administration of 3 x 2 Neurapas(R) balance tablets over a period of three days vs.

 placebo lead to an improvement in sleep architecture, especially an increase in deep sleep? 3.

 Does the administration of 3 x 2 Neurapas(R) balance tablets over a period of three days vs.

 placebo lead to an improvement in morning attentional performance? 4.

 Does the administration of 3 x 2 Neurapas(R) balance tablets over a period of three days vs.

 placebo lead to an improvement in morning well-being?.

